1 (e) Exemptions. – The following items, as described in Title 21 of the Code of Federal
2 Regulations, are exempt from these provisions:
3 (1) Human blood collection and storage bags.
4 (2) Apheresis and cell therapy blood kits and bags, including integral tubing."
5 SECTION 2. G.S. 130A-22(b3) reads as rewritten:
6 "(b3) The Secretary may impose an administrative penalty on a person who violates Article
7 19A or 19B Article 19A, 19B, or 19C of this Chapter or any rules adopted pursuant to Article
8 19A or 19B Article 19A, 19B, or 19C of this Chapter. Each day of a continuing violation is a
9 separate violation. The penalty shall not exceed five thousand dollars ($5,000) for each day the
10 violation continues for Article 19A of this Chapter. The penalty shall not exceed five thousand
11 dollars ($5,000) for each day the violation continues for Article 19B of this Chapter. The penalty
12 shall not exceed five thousand dollars ($5,000) for each day the violation continues for Article
13 19C of this Chapter. The penalty authorized by this section does not apply to a person who is not
14 required to be certified under Article 19A or 19B."
15 SECTION 3. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
16 law.
